column2: Patient John Doe, 45 years old, diagnosed with hypertension.
Jane Smith, 32, presented with acute bronchitis.
CT scan shows a small lesion in the left temporal lobe. Recommend follow-up MRI.
Patient complains of shortness of breath and chest pain. ECG normal.
Diabetic patient with HbA1c of 8.2%. Continue metformin and monitor.
Chronic back pain; prescribed ibuprofen 400mg every 8 hours.
Patient reports dizziness and palpitations. ECG shows atrial fibrillation.
History of asthma; patient using fluticasone inhaler twice daily.
Abdominal pain and vomiting. Ultrasound shows gallstones.
Chronic kidney disease stage 3; monitor creatinine and adjust meds.
